Fifth, the likelihood of invasions depends upon many factors, for example, regions of origin, regions of destination, human usage, likelihood of being transported, and sensitivity of invaded regions, which altogether influence the different stages of invasion: introduction, establishment, spread, and impacts (
 Donaldson et al., 2014; 
 Early et al., 2016; 
 Bellard et al., 2018; 
 Essl et al., 2018). The relevant factors should be considered for future studies.
